genresAdvancedInfo.name: maluku pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Maluku pop is a type of popular music that originated in the Maluku Islands, a group of islands in eastern Indonesia. It combines traditional Malukan music with modern pop sensibilities, featuring upbeat rhythms, catchy melodies, and lyrics sung in the local dialects. The genre has gained popularity in recent years, both in Indonesia and internationally.
